  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support Programme to Decentralisation Reform</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">By supporting the decentralisation of Uganda&#xBF;s political and administrative system, the objective of the project was to foster democratic progress and thus strengthen participation in the decision-making process. The project consisted of two key components. The first emphasised support for local development, mainly though phase II in the joint development-programme for Local Governance. Danish support was targeted capacity building and activities designed to improve local tax collection. The second key component contributed to strengthening of the industrial framework for decentralisation and included the Ministry of Local Government, Uganda&#xBF;s Union of local Governance and the national Local Governance Financial Commission. Danish support was coordinated along with activities of significant development-partners. The development programme for Local Governance was sponsored though earmarked budget-support. The programme contributed to the determination of a joint political framework for decentralisation, including a solid mechanism of evaluation. Finally, the programme played a key role in the development of a joint sector strategy for decentralisation; an investment plan for the local governances as well as sketching challenges and results of the investment plan.</narrative>
  </description>
